revision.text:
'''Bulletist''' or '''bulletism''' is an artistic process that involves shooting [[ink]] at a blank piece of [[paper]]<ref>"Surrealist Games." SourceryForge.org. N.p., n.d. Web. 3 Mar. 2011. {{cite web|url=http://sourceryforge.org/index.php/Surrealist_games |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-09-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011085449/http://sourceryforge.org/index.php/Surrealist_games |archivedate=2007-10-11 |df= }}.</ref>  The result is a type of [[Rorschach inkblot test|ink blot]]. The artist can then develop images based on what is seen. [[Salvador Dalí]] claimed to have invented this technique.{{Citation needed|date=January 2013}} [[Leonardo da Vinci]], however, suggested that "just as one can hear any desired syllable in the sound of a bell, so one can see any desired figure in the shape formed by throwing a sponge with ink against the wall."<ref>"Bulletism." glossary.com. Glossary.com, 2011. Web. 3 Mar. 2011. http://www.glossary.com/reference.php?q=Bulletism {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711101746/http://www.glossary.com/reference.php?q=Bulletism# |date=2011-07-11 }}.</ref>

