'''Plucky Brit''' is slang for a British athlete who is brave and determined, especially when success is unlikely.<ref name="theguardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/mar/19/uk-sport-olympic-funding-basketball-funding|title='This is a very dark day for sport' – funding appeals rejected by UK Sport &#124; Sport &#124; The Guardian|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=2014-04-02}}</ref><ref name="spiked-online">{{cite web|url=http://www.spiked-online.com/newsite/article/7141#.UuBi4tLFKt8|title=The year British sport got serious &#124; Sport &#124; spiked|publisher=spiked-online.com|accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Nicole Cooke suggests Plucky Brit can be slain |publisher= Times|date=|url= http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/sport/columnists/article2634278.ece|accessdate=2013-07-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= The art of failure |publisher= [[BBC]]|date=2005-07-25|url= http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/4707015.stm|accessdate=2013-07-12|first=Brian|last=Wheeler}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Eddie 'The Eagle' Edwards and the Cult of the Plucky Loser, 1988 |publisher= [[Financial Times]]|date=|url= http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/43c3a5ec-aab0-11dc-a779-0000779fd2ac.html#axzz2YnuITAfh|accessdate=2013-07-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Farewell to the 'Plucky Brit' syndrome... and good riddance |publisher= [[Daily Mail]]|date=2012-12-23|url= http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/article-2252604/Laura-Williamson-Farewell-Plucky-Brit-syndrome-good-riddance.html#ixzz2YnsG5wC7|accessdate=2013-07-12|location=London|first=Laura|last=Williamson}}</ref> The term is used in popular culture.<ref name="theguardian2">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2013/jul/13/britain-worlds-best-andy-murray|title=Like it or not, Andy Murray's win shows we're the best in the world &#124; Tim Lewis &#124; Sport &#124; The Observer|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref name="lawgazette">{{cite web|url=http://www.lawgazette.co.uk/analysis/being-british-and-a-good-sport-the-story-of-sport-and-the-law/66874.article|title=Being British and a ‘good sport’ - the story of ‘Sport and the Law’ &#124; News &#124; Law Society Gazette|publisher=lawgazette.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref name="time">{{cite news|url=http://olympics.time.com/2012/08/05/great-britains-olympic-golds-win-hope-lift-the-public-mood/|title=Great Britain&#8217;s Olympic Golds Win Hope, Lift the Public Mood &#124; TIME.com|publisher=olympics.time.com|accessdate=2014-02-09|date=2012-08-05}}</ref><ref name="spiked-online2">{{cite web|url=http://www.spiked-online.com/newsite/article/a_nation_of_winners_not_yet/13858#.Ut7x_NLFKt8|title=A nation of winners? Not yet &#124; Life &#124; Sport &#124; spiked|publisher=spiked-online.com|accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Andy Murray and the death of the plucky British loser |publisher= [[Channel 4]]|date=|url= http://www.channel4.com/news/andy-murray-tennis-australian-open-plucky-loser-paradigm|accessdate=2013-07-12}}</ref> Success in the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] challenged the stereotype of the British plucky loser.<ref>{{cite news|title= Plucky British loser reduced to highlights |work= [[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=2009-01-31|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/tennis/australianopen/4413777/Plucky-British-loser-reduced-to-highlights.html|accessdate=2013-07-12|location=London|first=Jasper|last=Gerard}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Britons: winners or losers? |publisher= [[YouGov]]|date=|url= http://yougov.co.uk/news/2012/08/21/britons-winners-or-losers/|accessdate=2013-07-12}}</ref> [[Chris Hoy]] stated “I think the Brits historically have got used to being the plucky losers. The attitude has been we'll support our lads and our lasses but we don't expect them to win anything. The teams go to the world cup in football and there are the usual tales of woe – losing penalty shoot-outs. It's like inevitable that the Brits are going to get beaten at some point. But I think that's there's a change in that culture in sport.”<ref name="english">{{cite web|url=http://www.english.rfi.fr/sports/20120813-london-2012-olympics-sets-standard-generation|title=London 2012 Olympics sets the standard for a generation - Report: London Olympic Games 2012 - RFI|publisher=english.rfi.fr|accessdate=2014-02-09}}</ref><ref name="telegraph">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/10085045/Olympics-has-turned-Britain-into-nation-of-winners-says-Hoy.html|title=Olympics has turned Britain into nation of winners says Hoy - Telegraph|publisher=telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=2014-02-09|location=London|first=David|last=Millward|date=2013-05-28}}</ref>
